      <hedline>
        <hl1>Let's Try Again on Health Care</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Esther Amaral letter calls for health insurance for all (Sept 24 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Toward Universal Coverage'' (editorial, Sept. 24):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Toward Universal Coverage'' (editorial, Sept. 24):</p>
        <p>I am a 76-year-old woman, but I still remember my mother saying, ''What we need in this country is socialized medicine for everyone.'' I later learned that the word ''socialized'' was a definite no-no, but my mother was a dyed-in-the-wool Democrat and never even flirted with Socialism.</p>
        <p>She just thought that medical care should be available to all who needed it. Foolish woman, she was!</p>
        <p>ESTHER AMARAL  Porterville, Calif., Sept. 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
